\subsubsection{Results}

In Figure \ref{timelengthavg} the average search times and average trajectory lengths of the runs of the test series are shown. The intelligent search system is significant faster than the uninformed search system and difference between the systems is even higher in the trajectory length. The reason for the greater difference in the trajectory length is that the switching of high-level tasks and the peek tasks, which both is done more often in the intelligent search system, cost time, but no distance is traveled there. The time of about 5 seconds per high-level task switch and 20 seconds per peek task adds up. The variance in the search runs is high, therefore the search times and trajectory lengths are shown in more detail in Figure \ref{search times} and \ref{search length}.
