\subfloat[]{\includegraphics[width=0.5\textwidth]{figures/example_runs/remote2.png}}
\end{tabular}
\caption{Possible starts of the exploration from starting pose 1}
\label{remotes}
\end{figure}

In Figure \ref{remotes} two search runs of setting 3 in the previous section are depicted. In the run shown in (a) the robot first enters room \textit{home3} and as both visited rooms have a low probability for containing the searched mouse, the smaller room \textit{home3} is searched. Only after that the room \textit{home2} is discovered and the mouse is found. In the run shown in (b) the room \textit{home2} is discovered first and the mouse is found quickly. 

