\end{tabular}
\caption{Possible starts of the exploration from starting pose 1}
\label{explore_split}
\end{figure}

In Figure \ref{wine1} a search for a wine glass hidden in the kitchen of the institute environment is shown. In this run the kitchen was the last room which is entered. Only the bathroom, which was visited first, no search was done. This is similar to the search for the mouse, where the robot prefers to searches a small, unlikely room before exploring a large, unlikely room. However, in the search for a toilet shown in Figure \ref{toilet} the robot only peeks in the rooms on the way and therefore efficiently finds the toilet. 

